#Summary1=(human1) After reading and napping on a bleak December night to forget the sorrow of losing Lenore, a rare and radiant maiden, a raven comes in through the window and perches above the chamber door, repeatedly saying 'Nevermore' when asked for its name and about whether the narrator will again clasp Lenore, upsetting the narrator greatly.

#Summary2=(claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022) A grief-stricken scholar, pondering over books late at night and mourning his lost Lenore, is visited by a mysterious raven who perches above his chamber door and responds "Nevermore" to his increasingly desperate questions, ultimately driving him to madness as the bird's shadow symbolically traps his soul forever.

#Summary3=(gpt4o) In "The Raven" by Edgar Allan Poe, a grieving man is visited by a mysterious raven that repeatedly utters the word "Nevermore," intensifying his sorrow over his lost love Lenore and leaving him in a state of despair as the bird's presence and ominous refrain haunt him, suggesting he will never escape his anguish.

#Summary4=(Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct; postedited) In this poem, a narrator is visited by a talking raven that repeats the word “Nevermore” in response to his questions, refusing to leave or provide comfort, and instead, remains perched on a bust of Pallas, echoing the word “Nevermore” repeatedly.

#Summary5=(Qwen2.5-3B-Instruct; postedited) The narrator recounts an eerie encounter with a raven that repeatedly croaks "nevermore," symbolizing loss and mourning as it sits outside his chamber door, casting a dark shadow over his contemplation.
#Text=THE RAVEN .
#Text=ONCE upon a midnight dreary , while I pondered , weak and weary , Over many a quaint and curious volume of forgotten lore —
#Text=While I nodded , nearly napping , suddenly there came a tapping , As of some one gently rapping , rapping at my chamber door .
#Text=" 'T is some visiter , " I muttered , " tapping at my chamber door —

#Text=But the silence was unbroken , and the stillness gave no token , And the only word there spoken was the whispered word ,  Lenore ? "

column1: #Text=This I whispered , and an echo murmured back the word , " Lenore ! " —
#Text=Merely this and nothing more .
#Text=Back into the chamber turning , all my soul within me burning , Soon again I heard a tapping something louder than before .
#Text=" Surely , " said I , " surely that is something at my window lattice ;
#Text=Much I marvelled this ungainly fowl to hear discourse so plainly ,
#Text=Though its answer little meaning — little relevancy bore ;

#Text=For we can not help agreeing that no living human being Ever yet was blessed with seeing bird above his chamber door — Bird or beast upon the sculptured bust above his chamber door , With such name as " Nevermore . "
#Text=But the Raven , sitting lonely on that placid bust , spoke only That one word , as if his soul in that one word he did outpour .
#Text=Nothing farther then he uttered ;
#Text=not a feather then he fluttered —
#Text=Till I scarcely more than muttered
#Text=" Other friends have flown before —

#Text=Then , upon the velvet sinking , I betook myself to linking Fancy unto fancy , thinking what this ominous bird of yore — What this grim , ungainly , ghastly , gaunt , and ominous bird of yore Meant in croaking  Nevermore . "

column1: #Text=This I sat engaged in guessing , but no syllable expressing To the fowl whose fiery eyes now burned into my bosom 's core ;
#Text=This and more I sat divining , with my head at ease reclining On the cushion 's velvet lining that the lamp - light gloated o'er ,
#Text=But whose velvet violet lining with the lamp - light gloating o'er She shall press , ah , nevermore !
#Text=Then , me thought , the air grew denser , perfumed from an unseen censer Swung by Seraphim whose foot - falls tinkled on the tufted floor .
#Text=" Wretch , " I cried , " thy God hath lent thee — by these angels he hath sent thee Respite — respite and nepenthe from thy memories of Lenore !
#Text=" Prophet ! " said I , " thing of evil !
#Text=" Prophet ! " said I , " thing of evil —
#Text=" Be that word our sign of parting , bird or fiend ! " I shrieked , upstarting —
#Text=" Get thee back into the tempest and the Night 's Plutonian shore !
#Text=And the Raven , never flitting , still is sitting , still is sitting On the pallid bust of Pallas just above my chamber door ;
#Text=And his eyes have all the seeming of a demon 's that is dreaming
#Text=And the lamp - light o'er him streaming throws his shadow on the floor ;
#Text=And my soul from out that shadow that lies floating on the floor Shall be lifted — nevermore !
